<h3>Email Content Best Practices</h3>
<ul>
<li><strong>One primary CTA per email.</strong> "Reserve Now" or "Order Online." Not both. Too many options reduce clicks.</li>
<li><strong>Use real food photography.</strong> Never use stock photos. Diners recognize generic food images instantly.</li>
<li><strong>Mobile-first design.</strong> 55% to 56% of restaurant emails open on mobile. Use a single-column layout. Buttons at least 44x44 pixels.</li>
<li><strong>Keep it short.</strong> 50 to 150 words for promotional emails. 200 to 300 words for newsletters. Restaurants are not publishing blog posts via email.</li>
<li><strong>Include your location and hours.</strong> Every email footer needs your address, phone number, and hours. Make it easy to find you.</li>
</ul>
